msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.corrcoef:40
msgid ""
"Data-type of the result. By default, the return data-type will have at least "
"`numpy.float64` precision."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.corrcoef:0
msgid "Returns"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.corrcoef:54
msgid "**R**"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.corrcoef:-1
msgid "ndarray"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.corrcoef:48
msgid "The correlation coefficient matrix of the variables."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.corrcoef:59
msgid ":obj:`cov`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.corrcoef:60
msgid "Covariance matrix"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.corrcoef:64
msgid "Notes"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.corrcoef:65
msgid ""
"Due to floating point rounding the resulting array may not be Hermitian, the "
"diagonal elements may not be 1, and the elements may not satisfy the "
"inequality abs(a) <= 1. The real and imaginary parts are clipped to the "
"interval [-1,  1] in an attempt to improve on that situation but is not much "
"help in the complex case."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.corrcoef:71
msgid ""
"This function accepts but discards arguments `bias` and `ddof`.  This is for "
"backwards compatibility with previous versions of this function.  These "
"arguments had no effect on the return values of the function and can be "
"safely ignored in this and previous versions of numpy."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.corrcoef:78
msgid "Examples"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.corrcoef:79
msgid ""
"In this example we generate two random arrays, ``xarr`` and ``yarr``, and "
"compute the row-wise and column-wise Pearson correlation coefficients, "
"``R``. Since ``rowvar`` is  true by  default, we first find the row-wise "
"Pearson correlation coefficients between the variables of ``xarr``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.corrcoef:97
msgid ""
"If we add another set of variables and observations ``yarr``, we can compute "
"the row-wise Pearson correlation coefficients between the variables in "
"``xarr`` and ``yarr``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../../../../../.conda/lib/python3.10/site-packages/numpy/__init__.py:docstring
#: of numpy.corrcoef:121
msgid ""
"Finally if we use the option ``rowvar=False``, the columns are now being "
"treated as the variables and we will find the column-wise Pearson "
"correlation coefficients between variables in ``xarr`` and ``yarr``."
msgstr ""
